CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. B10 reads: "Chi Delta Mu Fraternity Entertains Lavishly - Dr. Robert Bolden, far right; Mrs. Bolden, right front, and guests" Portion of accompanying article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. A7 by Toki Schalk Johnson reads:"Wednesday brought forth the annual dinner dance given by the Chi Delta Mu Fraternity in beautifully decorated New Arena."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, including Rev. Le Roy Patrick, second from left front and Dr. Robert Bolden, right rear, and five women, including Mrs. Bolden right front, seated at rectangular banquet table for Chi Delta Mu dinner dance in New Arena Supper Club
